@startuml
title Viaverse Chat / Messaging — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nChat list\nConversation screen\nContext card" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nConversation API\nMessage API" as BFF
component "MessagingController" as Controller
component "Messaging Use Cases\nCreateConversation\nSendMessage\nMarkRead\nReportMessage" as UseCases
component "Messaging Policies\nparticipants\ncontext state\ncontact sharing\nreporting" as Policy
component "Ports\nConversationRepo\nMessageRepo\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "marketplace-service\nquote/job context\nallowed sharing state" as Marketplace
component "media-service\nattachments\nmoderation status" as Media
database "PostgreSQL + Cassandra\nconversation metadata\nmessages/read models" as DB
component "notification-service\nrecipient alerts" as Notify
component "Safety / Moderation\ncontact sharing\nreports\nrisk signals" as Safety
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nMessageSent\nMessageReported\nSupportEscalationRequested" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policy : validate
Policy --> Ports : ports
Policy --> Marketplace : context check
UseCases --> Media : attach refs
Ports --> DB : persist/read model
UseCases --> Safety : scan/report
UseCases --> Notify : notify recipient
UseCases --> Kafka : outbox events

note bottom
Future E2EE-ready boundary should be preserved,
but initial implementation can use server-stored messages
with strict policy, audit and report flows.
end note
@enduml
